headlines.description: — Brook Lopez scored 26 points, Khris Middleton and Jevon Carter each added 24 points and the Milwaukee Bucks beat the Orlando Magic 134-123 on Tuesday night for their 18th win in 19 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks beat Magic 134-123 for 18th win in 19 games

headlines.description: — Daniel Gafford converted a putback of Bradley Beal's airball at the buzzer, and the Washington Wizards handed the Detroit Pistons their ninth straight loss, 119-117 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gafford's putback gives Wizards 119-117 win over Pistons

events.name: Charlotte Hornets at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Needing two overtimes to get by Boston two nights earlier left the New York Knicks low on fuel when they returned home.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hornets snap Knicks' 9-game win streak with 112-105 victory

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid scored 39 points, Tyrese Maxey added 27 and the Philadelphia 76ers beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 117-94 on Tuesday night, despite playing without star James Harden.
— Mikal Bridges scored 30 points, Spencer Dinwiddie added 23 and the Brooklyn Nets had a big third quarter to beat the Houston Rockets 118-96 on Tuesday night for their third straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bridges has 30 points, Nets beat Rockets for 3rd straight

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 33 points, Josh Giddey had the seventh triple-double of his career and third of the season, and the Oklahoma City Thunder beat the Golden State Warriors 137-128 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander, Giddey lead Thunder past Warriors

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving hit a clutch 3-pointer and scored 17 of his 33 points in the fourth quarter, and Luka Doncic added 29 points and 10 rebounds as the Dallas Mavericks beat the short-handed Utah Jazz 120-116 Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Irving's late run helps push Mavericks past Jazz 120-116

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis had 30 points and 22 rebounds, Dennis Schröder added 17 points and nine assists and the Los Angeles Lakers moved into ninth place in the Western Conference with a 112-103 victory over the Memphis Grizzlies on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony Davis leads Lakers past Grizz without Ja, 112-103
